We were, uh,
wondering whether

24:26.730 --> 24:27.890
For three weeks? Why?

24:27.930 --> 24:29.898
Chumhum needs some
work on a case.

24:29.930 --> 24:31.591
So, we do it
from our new office.

24:31.630 --> 24:32.722
(car alarm chirps)

24:32.770 --> 24:34.829
Look, we can't keep
skulking around.

24:34.870 --> 24:37.065
We have to cut the cord
at some pomt.
ROBYN:
I agree.

24:37.100 --> 24:38.829
We need to get going.
Tell her the real reason.

24:40.210 --> 24:42.007
People want to wait
for bonuses.

24:42.040 --> 24:43.576
Oh, come on!

24:43.610 --> 24:44.577
It's $1 million
between us.

24:44.610 --> 24:46.168
If we walk out before
the first of the month,

24:46.210 --> 24:47.177
they'll never pay us.

24:47.210 --> 24:48.575
A lot of us
are counting on

24:48.620 --> 24:49.712
that money for
start-up costs.

24:49.750 --> 24:50.717
We can't keep fooling
the partners.

24:50.750 --> 24:52.149
We can't keep fooling Will.

24:55.060 --> 24:56.857
Do we have a problem?

24:56.890 --> 24:59.984
No. But you were all right
waiting a week to leave

25:00.030 --> 25:01.725
after your case
was finished,

25:01.760 --> 25:04.524
but you're not all right
when it's our issue?

25:04.570 --> 25:05.867
It's a death row case.

25:05.900 --> 25:08.164
Okay, let's not make it
a big issue.

25:08.200 --> 25:11.533
Listen, the difference here
is two weeks.

25:11.570 --> 25:14.505
Let's just put it up to a vote
to the others, okay?

25:17.780 --> 25:19.145
(car alarm wailing)

25:25.850 --> 25:26.942
Hey, Tommy.

25:26.990 --> 25:29.185
Who are you?

25:29.220 --> 25:31.029
Kalinda.
Robyn.

25:31.060 --> 25:32.948
I don't know who you guys
are looking for.

25:32.990 --> 25:33.854
My name isn't Tommy.
It is.

25:33.900 --> 25:35.720
Tommy Diehause.

25:35.760 --> 25:38.297
Sad. You win
a whole new identity,

25:38.330 --> 25:39.991
but you still can't
resist being a thief.

25:40.030 --> 25:43.568
(sirens approaching)

25:43.610 --> 25:46.067
Look, I don't know
how you guys found me,

25:46.110 --> 25:48.305
but I told the truth
at Eddie's trial.

25:48.340 --> 25:49.329
He killed those girls.

25:49.380 --> 25:50.972
He was only trying
to jack their car,

25:51.010 --> 25:52.978
but they fought him and
pulled off his ski mask,

25:53.010 --> 25:54.841
and that's why he had
to kill them.

25:54.880 --> 25:56.916
Come on, Tommy, why would
anyone confess to you?

25:56.950 --> 25:58.838
You have snitch
written all over you.
Yeah.

26:00.390 --> 26:02.756
But how'd I know
about the ski mask

26:02.790 --> 26:04.189
if Eddie
didn't tell me, huh?

26:04.230 --> 26:07.893
The police never told
anyone about that little detail.

26:07.930 --> 26:09.295
Maybe you heard it
from the real killer.

26:09.330 --> 26:10.968
I did hear it
from the real killer:

26:11.000 --> 26:14.060
your client.

26:14.100 --> 26:15.135
Alicia, Alicia.

26:15.170 --> 26:16.660
Kalinda found
the snitch,

26:16.700 --> 26:18.065
but he's sticking
to his story.

26:18.110 --> 26:19.702
Damn.
Does she believe him?

26:19.740 --> 26:21.139
No. She thinks
there might be

26:21.180 --> 26:22.977
another way to
get him, though.

26:23.010 --> 26:25.001
Are you okay?

26:25.050 --> 26:28.144
The parking garage meet?

26:28.180 --> 26:29.875
Sure. We're fine.

26:29.920 --> 26:31.387
MONICA:
Hello?

26:31.420 --> 26:32.944
Can someone help me, please?

26:32.990 --> 26:34.582
I can't see anything.

26:36.420 --> 26:38.229
(door b
an
Oh! gs)

26:38.260 --> 26:40.990
Is anyone around?

26:41.030 --> 26:42.054
Thank you.

26:42.100 --> 26:43.055
WILL:
Alicia.

26:43.100 --> 26:44.624
Do you have a minute?

26:44.670 --> 26:45.762
Sure.

26:58.080 --> 26:59.638
What's wrong?

26:59.680 --> 27:01.409
DAVID: We looked into
the company's phones.

27:01.450 --> 27:02.815
Over the past month,

27:02.850 --> 27:03.885
the fourth-year associates
have called

27:03.920 --> 27:05.785
our top clients
a dozen times each.

27:05.820 --> 27:07.879
DIANE: We're worried they're
thinking of leaving with them.

27:07.920 --> 27:09.353
Do you have
any insight?

27:11.330 --> 27:13.992
No.

27:14.030 --> 27:16.919
We called the clients, but
they're being tight-lipped,

27:16.960 --> 27:19.269
said they have no plans of
leaving at the present time.

27:19.300 --> 27:21.188
DAVID: Which is known as
"preservmg their options."

27:21.240 --> 27:23.037
I say we move
past metadata

27:23.070 --> 27:23.968
and access their texts.

27:24.010 --> 27:25.102
Can we do that?

27:25.140 --> 27:26.232
Where's Kalinda?

27:26.270 --> 27:28.238
DAVID: Kalinda's
sympathetic with them.

27:28.280 --> 27:30.840
Yes, we can do that.
They're our phones.

27:30.880 --> 27:31.949
We own the texts.

27:31.980 --> 27:33.379
WILL: Alicia, you're
friends with Cary.

27:33.410 --> 27:35.048
Are you hearing anything at all?

27:35.080 --> 27:38.686
No. Not since the fourth-years
tried to scare us.

27:38.720 --> 27:40.347
It would be helpful if you
could get closer to them.

27:40.390 --> 27:41.186
WILL:
Find out if they're happy,

27:41.220 --> 27:43.359
and whether
we should be worried.

27:45.330 --> 27:47.025
Sure.

28:00.170 --> 28:02.138
KLUGER:
Okay, here's my problem:

28:02.180 --> 28:05.445
I have two medical
reports conducted by

28:05.480 --> 28:07.107
two different doctors--

28:07.150 --> 28:09.311
one for the plaintiff,
one for the defense--

28:09.350 --> 28:11.238
and surprisingly, they
tell two different stories.

28:11.290 --> 28:13.246
Your Honor,
may I suggest...

28:13.290 --> 28:15.417
That Mr. Fornum be preserved
as a rebuttal witness?

28:15.460 --> 28:17.724
LENA:
Your Honor, we withdraw

28:17.760 --> 28:19.921
our medical report on the
offender's physical condition

28:19.960 --> 28:22.121
and stipulate to the truth
of the plaintiff's report.

28:24.500 --> 28:25.728
Excuse me?

28:25.770 --> 28:27.067
In addition, we stipulate

28:27.100 --> 28:29.034
to everything testified in
Mr. Fornum's deposition.

28:29.070 --> 28:30.367
So let me get
this straight.

28:30.400 --> 28:31.731
You've decided that
it's better to execute

28:31.770 --> 28:33.738
Mr._ Fornum than
to Win your lawswt?

28:33.780 --> 28:34.974
We also have the warden

28:35.010 --> 28:36.375
from the Indiana State Prison

28:36.410 --> 28:37.968
who will swear to changes

28:38.010 --> 28:40.478
in the lethal injection protocol
so at to reduce the pain

28:40.510 --> 28:41.477
associated therewith.

28:41.520 --> 28:42.316
I imagine, Mr. Gardner,

28:42.350 --> 28:44.739
you would like to depose
said warden?

28:44.790 --> 28:46.348
Definitely, Your Honor.
Either way,

28:46.390 --> 28:48.415
there's no reason to delay
this execution anymore.

28:48.460 --> 28:51.429
If you so stipulate,
I suppose that's true.

28:51.460 --> 28:53.189
(gavelbangs)

28:56.060 --> 28:58.164
ROBYN:
Ms. Lockhart?

28:59.500 --> 29:01.092
Eddie didn't do it.

29:01.140 --> 29:02.095
I agree.

29:02.140 --> 29:03.937
How do we prove it?

29:03.970 --> 29:05.835
The snitch testified
about the ski mask,

29:05.870 --> 29:08.270
something he could only know
from the killer, right?

29:08.310 --> 29:10.847
But when I was at Treasury,
we looked into prison brokers.

29:10.880 --> 29:12.279
Prison. . .?
Brokers.

29:12.310 --> 29:14.278
They're police insiders who sell
information to prisoners

29:14.320 --> 29:17.016
so that they can snitch
on their cell mates in exchange

29:17.050 --> 29:18.278
for a lighter sentence.

29:18.320 --> 29:23.110
You think Diehause got the ski
mask information from a broker?

29:23.160 --> 29:25.025
I don't know. Maybe.

29:27.060 --> 29:28.322
But he'll just deny it.

29:28.360 --> 29:29.497
If we go to him.

29:29.530 --> 29:32.021
But what if we go
after the broker?

29:34.400 --> 29:38.109
Tommy Diehause snitched
for our office three times.

29:38.140 --> 29:40.233
So we want to find someone
on all three cases.

29:40.270 --> 29:42.272
Yeah, like a police officer,
forensic investigator.

29:42.310 --> 29:43.902
Good luck.

29:43.950 --> 29:46.271
You're not gonna help us?

29:54.920 --> 29:57.821
(talking quietly)

30:02.230 --> 30:04.027
Yeah.

30:07.230 --> 30:09.892
MAN:
Sir?

30:11.940 --> 30:14.374
Why do you think Alicia's
leaving Lockhart/Gardner?

30:14.410 --> 30:15.434
Why do I think?

30:15.480 --> 30:17.300
Because she wants
to make something of herself.

30:17.340 --> 30:18.500
Not about Will?

30:21.480 --> 30:23.914
Well, I-I wouldn't presume.

30:23.950 --> 30:26.919
And, uh...

30:26.950 --> 30:29.555
you think the optics are wrong
with Marilyn?

30:29.590 --> 30:32.081
Yes.

30:32.130 --> 30:36.191
Photos of you with her
would give the wrong impression.

30:36.230 --> 30:38.164
Okay.

30:40.170 --> 30:42.035
Promote her.

30:43.640 --> 30:45.164
No. No cops in common,

30:45.210 --> 30:46.234
_ no forensic _
investigators, nothing.

30:46.270 --> 30:48.602
We're still looking.

30:48.640 --> 30:49.902
(sighs)

30:49.940 --> 30:51.271
Okay.

30:51.310 --> 30:54.040
The execution is on
for tonight.

30:55.280 --> 30:57.885
Who typed up
your crime report?

30:57.920 --> 31:00.241
What?

31:00.290 --> 31:03.555
Who was_ the clerk
on your crime report?

31:03.590 --> 31:06.252
Bottom of the page, there.

31:16.070 --> 31:18.334
The typist.

31:23.140 --> 31:24.368
Thank you, so much,
Ms. Munn,

31:24.410 --> 31:26.071
for coming in on
such short notice.

31:26.110 --> 31:28.271
Oh, no problem, but I'm-I'm
not sure how I can help.

31:28.320 --> 31:29.548
I just type.

31:29.580 --> 31:31.286
I don't actually catch
the bad guys.

31:31.320 --> 31:33.584
Actually, uh, we
want to help you.

31:33.620 --> 31:35.087
Really? How do you want
to do that?

31:35.120 --> 31:37.384
We want to keep
you out of jail.

31:37.420 --> 31:40.127
We discovered your brother
works as a prison guard,

31:40.160 --> 31:42.094
and that's how you sell
information to snitches.

31:45.070 --> 31:47.459
We are meeting next
with Tommy Diehause,

31:47.500 --> 31:49.934
and one of you is gonna
turn on the other.

31:49.970 --> 31:52.302
That's the problem
with working with

31:52.340 --> 31:54.433
a snitch, Ms. Munn:
they like to snitch.

31:55.980 --> 31:58.039
So I would start talking first.

31:59.080 --> 32:00.502
(knocking)

32:00.550 --> 32:02.211
What do you want?

32:02.250 --> 32:04.514
ZACH: Did Stiles talk to
you yesterday at school?

32:04.550 --> 32:06.518
What? Drew Stiles?

32:06.550 --> 32:07.642
Yeah. Why?

32:07.690 --> 32:09.988
What'd he say?

32:10.020 --> 32:12.488
Nothing. He's disgusting.

32:12.530 --> 32:13.588
I know. What'd he say?

32:13.630 --> 32:15.450
Did you say something
to your friends?

32:15.500 --> 32:17.127
No. Why?

32:17.160 --> 32:19.492
They're all trying
to talk to me now.

32:23.740 --> 32:26.004
What are you doing?

32:34.150 --> 32:36.414
What is this?

32:46.130 --> 32:49.122
ALICIA: Kids, hurry up!
Your ride's here!

32:51.330 --> 32:52.627
(knocking)

32:54.540 --> 32:57.293
Can we talk?

32:57.340 --> 32:59.558
Uh, my mistake.

32:59.610 --> 33:01.339
I have to get to work.

33:01.380 --> 33:03.302
You were in with the
partners yesterday.

33:03.340 --> 33:05.069
What did they say?

33:05.110 --> 33:06.099
Nothing.

33:07.810 --> 33:09.346
Alicia.

33:09.380 --> 33:10.677
(door closes)

33:10.720 --> 33:13.041
We need to leave
by the end of the week.

33:13.090 --> 33:15.058
They said that?
No, I'm saying it.

33:15.090 --> 33:16.250
I'm still a partner here.

33:16.290 --> 33:18.178
And I'm stuck in the middle.

33:18.230 --> 33:19.788
I have a fiduciary
responsibility

33:19.830 --> 33:20.626
to Lockhart/Gardner.

33:20.660 --> 33:23.049
And I am opening myself up
to a lawsuit

33:23.100 --> 33:24.727
just by talking
to you about anything.

33:24.770 --> 33:26.567
We need to leave.
Look.

33:26.600 --> 33:29.137
One of the things
we said we didn't like

33:29.170 --> 33:31.138
about Lockhart/Gardner was
how decisions were made

33:31.170 --> 33:33.206
by fiat: by
Will and Diane.

33:33.240 --> 33:36.209
We said we wanted to run
things democratically.

33:36.240 --> 33:38.049
And we all voted
to wait three weeks.

33:39.110 --> 33:40.805
Would we take this case?

33:40.850 --> 33:42.477
This death row case.

33:42.520 --> 33:43.771
I don't know.

33:43.820 --> 33:44.787
Probably. Why not?

33:44.820 --> 33:45.809
It's pro bono.

33:45.850 --> 33:47.738
50 partner hours.

33:47.790 --> 33:49.655
We would be afraid
of going broke.

33:49.690 --> 33:50.657
Yeah, but
Lockhart/Gardner

33:50.690 --> 33:52.453
didn't take
death row cases

33:52.490 --> 33:54.526
until its sixth
or seventh year.

33:59.530 --> 34:01.339
Are you having
second thoughts?

34:01.370 --> 34:04.430
I don't know.

34:04.470 --> 34:07.439
I like watching
Diane and Will work.

34:09.180 --> 34:10.772
They care.
Alicia.

34:10.810 --> 34:13.244
You and I are
the new Will and Diane.

34:20.850 --> 34:22.488
Don't use the company phones.

34:22.520 --> 34:24.181
They're accessing the data.

34:24.230 --> 34:25.629
I have a deposition.

34:26.990 --> 34:29.788
BARKIN: Very simply, the medical
team thought they could put

34:29.830 --> 34:32.526
an IV in the offender's
arm, but they were wrong.

34:32.570 --> 34:35.095
And how will tonight's
execution be different?

34:35.140 --> 34:36.869
We will do a better job
hydrating Mr. Fornum

34:36.900 --> 34:39.164
and using warm compresses
to raise his veins.

34:39.210 --> 34:41.531
And we will place
the I.V. in his foot.

34:41.580 --> 34:43.332
And you didn't do this
the last time?

34:43.380 --> 34:44.506
We would've.

34:44.550 --> 34:45.847
But the execution
was halted.

34:45.880 --> 34:47.575
And I didn't
superwse it.

34:47.610 --> 34:49.510
So, you weren't present
during the last attempt?

34:49.550 --> 34:51.188
Not all the time.

34:51.220 --> 34:53.643
We had a late arrival
of potassium chloride.

34:53.690 --> 34:56.579
We've had difficulties with the
supply of this drug in the past,

34:56.620 --> 34:59.384
so I supervised and
witnessed its removal

34:59.430 --> 35:01.159
from an overnight
pouch and placement

35:01.200 --> 35:02.098
in the intravenous tubing.

35:02.130 --> 35:03.859
However, we will have
greater control...

35:03.900 --> 35:06.164
(whispers):
What?

35:06.200 --> 35:07.622
I've ordered
the staff...

35:07.670 --> 35:10.491
This court seems to be all
Eddie Alan Fornum all the time.

35:10.540 --> 35:11.700
DIANE:
Yes, His Honor Manfreddi

35:11.740 --> 35:15.471
referred this death row appeal
to your court, Your Honor,

35:15.510 --> 35:17.239
um...

35:17.280 --> 35:19.339
given that you were
already hearing

35:19.380 --> 35:20.540
the Eighth Amendment appeal.

35:20.580 --> 35:22.241
Luclq me. All right.

35:22.280 --> 35:24.248
So you're ten hours away
from an execution.

35:24.290 --> 35:25.484
What do you got for me?

35:27.690 --> 35:29.851
We'd like to call a witness.

35:31.260 --> 35:34.252
DIANE: You testified at
Edward Alan Fornum's trial?

35:34.300 --> 35:35.289
Yes.

35:35.330 --> 35:36.558
And you testified

35:36.600 --> 35:38.659
that he confessed to
the double murder?

35:38.700 --> 35:39.792
Yes.

35:39.830 --> 35:41.331
And you would
like to now

35:41.370 --> 35:42.439
withdraw that testimony?

35:43.770 --> 35:45.328
Yes.
As far as you know,

35:45.370 --> 35:47.907
Eddie Fornum is innocent?

35:47.940 --> 35:49.737
Yes.

35:49.780 --> 35:51.577
And you received the information
to condemn him

35:51.610 --> 35:53.339
from the brother of

35:53.380 --> 35:55.575
that woman there--
Leslie Munn?

35:55.620 --> 35:57.212
Yes.
Is there anything else

35:57.250 --> 35:59.343
you would like to say?

36:01.260 --> 36:03.512
No.

36:06.290 --> 36:08.394
You know, I didn't plan
on judging this appeal,

36:08.430 --> 36:11.297
but you bring me that snitch
who changes his testimony

36:11.330 --> 36:14.538
after almost a decade?

36:14.570 --> 36:16.265
Now... (sighs)
now I'm sorry,

36:16.300 --> 36:17.460
Ms. Lockhart, I'm sorry,

36:17.500 --> 36:21.334
but, uh, an appeal
of actual innocence

36:21.380 --> 36:23.234
after years
of appeals and decisions

36:23.280 --> 36:26.204
and-and delays has to stand on

36:26.250 --> 36:28.969
much more ground than
an indecisive snitch.

36:29.020 --> 36:30.214
Your Honor...
No.

36:30.250 --> 36:31.410
At a certain point,

36:31.450 --> 36:35.352
it has to be over,
judgments must stand.

36:35.390 --> 36:36.755
God forgive me...

36:36.790 --> 36:38.678
I find for the state.

36:38.730 --> 36:40.618
Execution will proceed.

36:40.660 --> 36:42.651
(gavelbangs)

36:45.300 --> 36:48.565
GUARD:
Eddie, I need you to stand.

36:50.800 --> 36:52.802
Eddie, please.

37:02.380 --> 37:04.814
Place your hands
out in front of you.

37:13.360 --> 37:15.351
Turn around, please.

37:25.310 --> 37:27.301
You know the way, Eddie.

37:35.480 --> 37:37.414
You wanted to see me, Mr. Gold?

37:37.450 --> 37:38.747
Oh, yes. Hi, Marilyn.

37:38.790 --> 37:39.848
How are you?
Good.

37:39.890 --> 37:42.279
I think we're off to a great
start, don't you think?

37:42.320 --> 37:43.014
I do, I do.

37:43.060 --> 37:45.028
And I have some good news.

37:45.060 --> 37:48.518
Peter wants to promote you
to the Transit Authority...

37:48.560 --> 37:49.720
Board.

37:49.760 --> 37:51.398
I...

37:51.430 --> 37:52.465
I'm sorry, what?

37:52.500 --> 37:54.559
Yes, uh, an opening has

37:54.600 --> 37:57.660
opened up
on the Transit Authority Board,

37:57.700 --> 38:01.409
uh, where you will have
authority... over transit.

38:02.740 --> 38:04.298
Congratulations.

38:04.350 --> 38:05.806
Did I do something wrong?

38:05.850 --> 38:07.772
No, you did something right.

38:07.810 --> 38:09.778
It's a promotion.

38:11.590 --> 38:13.546
No, Marilyn.

38:13.590 --> 38:14.989
Peter promoted you.

38:15.020 --> 38:17.818
If he'd wanted to tell you
that himself, he would have.

38:19.830 --> 38:22.390
You guys are
making a mistake.

38:22.430 --> 38:24.318
Maybe.

38:24.370 --> 38:26.998
You have a good evening.

38:29.070 --> 38:31.095
(door closes)

38:31.140 --> 38:32.459
How did it go?

38:32.510 --> 38:33.761
Well.

38:33.810 --> 38:35.732
She took it like a pro.

38:35.780 --> 38:38.578
She's right, you know, we
need a new chief of staff.

38:38.610 --> 38:40.043
She's not right, she's anal.

38:40.080 --> 38:43.049
Well, anal's what
we need right now.

38:43.080 --> 38:44.718
Did I just say that?

38:44.750 --> 38:45.842
Yes.

38:45.890 --> 38:47.346
Our new state motto?

38:47.390 --> 38:48.709
(laughs)

38:48.760 --> 38:50.409
I'll make up a list.

38:50.460 --> 38:52.849
Why don't you do it?

38:52.890 --> 38:55.120
What? Be chief of staff?

38:55.160 --> 38:56.388
(laughs)

38:56.430 --> 38:58.569
But I...

38:58.600 --> 39:00.989
I'm working on
your next campaign, sir.

39:01.030 --> 39:03.965
My next campaign is
here in this office.

39:04.000 --> 39:06.400
I screw that up, there's
nowhere to go but down.

39:16.880 --> 39:18.745
You going tonight?

39:18.790 --> 39:20.781
No.

39:23.160 --> 39:25.025
We did everything
we could.

39:25.060 --> 39:27.051
Not everything.

39:56.190 --> 39:59.853
(metal clinking)

40:02.830 --> 40:04.821
(footsteps approaching)

40:09.240 --> 40:12.209
We want to put an I.V.
in early, Eddie,

40:12.240 --> 40:16.028
so there isn't the same
confu5ion at midnight.

40:16.080 --> 40:18.105
Tell us if you
feel any pain.

40:18.140 --> 40:19.175
You should feel

40:19.210 --> 40:21.440
a small pinprick as we attempt

40:21.480 --> 40:24.711
to put in the I.V.

40:24.750 --> 40:27.082
The monitor you see
above your ankle

40:27.120 --> 40:28.144
is a VeinMapper.

40:28.190 --> 40:31.819
It uses ultraviolet imaging
to help find veins.

40:40.130 --> 40:42.928
(groans softly)
Okay, the pain should be
over in a minute, Eddie.

40:42.970 --> 40:43.937
(door opens)

40:43.970 --> 40:46.939
Warden, excuse me.

40:46.970 --> 40:49.006
What?
There's somebody
out here for you.

40:50.240 --> 40:51.639
(sighs)

40:53.650 --> 40:55.948
I'll be right back
with you, Eddie.

40:59.550 --> 41:00.812
Excuse me.

41:00.850 --> 41:02.488
We're in the midst
of a protocol. What is it?

41:02.520 --> 41:03.680
Yes, our apologies, sir.

41:03.720 --> 41:06.052
My name is Agent Lionel Franklin
from the South Bend office

41:06.090 --> 41:08.058
of the Drug Enforcement
Administration.

41:08.090 --> 41:10.092
It's come to our attention
that you've transported

41:10.130 --> 41:12.462
toxic chemicals
through the US. Postal Service.

41:14.270 --> 41:15.737
Are you serious?

41:15.770 --> 41:19.206
It's a direct violation
of 49 U.S.C. 5101.

41:19.240 --> 41:21.572
Have you transported
any such chemicals?

41:21.610 --> 41:23.999
BARKIN: We use potassium
chloride in our L.I. protocol,

41:24.040 --> 41:25.940
and, yes, we transferred it
by overnight post.

41:25.980 --> 41:28.642
FRANKLIN: I'm gonna have to
confiscate those chemicals.

41:28.680 --> 41:30.841
*

41:44.700 --> 41:48.534
The governor has put
the execution on hold, Eddie.

41:48.570 --> 41:50.891
They don't want
to try a third time.

41:52.910 --> 41:54.901
It's over, Eddie.

41:59.180 --> 42:01.239
Thank you. Thank you.

42:04.620 --> 42:06.918
* With eyes open

42:06.950 --> 42:10.317
* I was having a dream

42:10.360 --> 42:14.854
* And as real as it seemed...

42:14.900 --> 42:16.697
Good work.

42:16.730 --> 42:18.152
ALICIA:
Thanks.

42:18.200 --> 42:20.623
Were you the one
who called the DEA?

42:20.670 --> 42:22.991
Now, what would
make you think that?

42:23.040 --> 42:24.132
It was a smart move.

42:24.170 --> 42:25.307
Have some?

42:25.340 --> 42:27.729
* I remember your face...

42:29.210 --> 42:30.575
Will?

42:32.850 --> 42:35.045
I need to tell you something.

42:35.080 --> 42:36.342
No, you don't, Alicia.

42:36.380 --> 42:38.917
Look, I know why
you didn't call, and it's okay.

42:38.950 --> 42:41.680
We were on a merry-go-round
and we needed to get off,

42:41.720 --> 42:43.187
so we're off.

42:48.630 --> 42:49.699
Don't end up hating me.

42:49.730 --> 42:52.290
What?

42:53.330 --> 42:56.094
Nothing. Have a good night.

42:56.140 --> 42:58.096
Are you sure you
don't want some?

42:58.140 --> 42:59.266
(laughs)

42:59.310 --> 43:00.334
No, I'm good.

43:07.380 --> 43:09.575
(Will and Diane
laughing, chattering)
